abraflexi-webhook-acceptor (1.3.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  [ Vitex ]
  * Add Kafka storage backend (per-evidence topics via php-rdkafka)
  * Add Redis Streams storage backend (per-evidence streams via php-redis)
  * Add MongoDB storage backend (per-evidence collections via php-mongodb)
  * Expand saver interface with saveWebhookData, getLastProcessedVersion,
    saveLastProcessedVersion methods
  * Add debian packages: -kafka, -redis, -mongodb
  * Add Ansible playbooks for test infrastructure provisioning
  * Add integration test script (tests/test_all_backends.php)
  * Upgrade mongodb/mongodb to ^2.0 for ext-mongodb 2.0 compatibility
  * php 8.4 update
  * Add invoice metastate detection (settled, remind1/2/3, penalised, storno,
    inventory) via InvoiceMetaStateResolver; metastates are appended to
    changes_cache as synthetic rows sharing the originating @operation
    field, so multiflexi-event-processor can match event_rule on them
    without any changes to the event processor itself
  * Widen changes_cache.operation beyond create/update/delete and add a
    surrogate autoincrement key (changes_cache.id) so metastate rows can
    share an `inversion` with the update that produced them
  * Add invoice_state_cache table to track last known payment/reminder
    field values per invoice for diffing
  * Require vitexsoftware/abraflexi-php; add ABRAFLEXI_* to .env.template

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:49:49 +0200

